Chinese smartphone brand OPPO officially launched their latest series, the OPPO Reno 2F in Nairobi on Monday. The device has four back cameras, the main 48MP camera with an f/1.79 aperture, an 8MP wide-angle camera with an f.2.2 aperture and two 2MP cameras where one is a mono camera and the other a secondary camera. It has a motorised 16MP selfie camera with an f/2.0 aperture. The Reno 2F is powered by the MediaTek Helio P70 chipset which is coupled with ARMâ€™s Mali-G72 MP3. It also comes with 8GB of RAM, 128GB of internal storage, 4,000 mAh battery with fast charging support feature, 16MP front camera, in-display fingerprint sensor, ColorOS 6.1 based on Android 9.0 Pie and 4G LTE support. The Head of Marketing and PR, Muthoni Wachira said OPPO aims to advance their 5G devices and in this they have has already got new and renewed partnerships with companies like Google and Qualcomm. OPPO is currently ranked number five smartphone brand worldwide with a global market share of 8.9 percent. Samsung and Huawei brands top the list with market share of 22.9 percent and 16.7 percent respectively all in 2019 Q2. The device will be available locally in various Oppo branded retail stores across the country and from online store.